[There are 16 hemagglutinin (H1-16) and 9 neuraminidase (N1-9) subtypes of influenza A virus. The diagnostic techniques applicable for their identification in collected samples as well as other, extensive information on avian influenza diagnosis and vaccines is available in OIE's terrestrial manual at http://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Health_standards/tahm/2.03.04_AI.pdf.

Results of the laboratory tests of the samples collected from widgeons' droppings from Kamerik, identifying the N type, are requested. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3008120,104.]
